aine River]], Quebec\n*** [[Savane River (Caldwell River tributary)|Savane River]], Quebec\n** [[Ashberish River]], Quebec\n** [[Touladi River]], Quebec\n*** [[Aigles River (Touladi River tributary)|Aigles River]], Quebec\n**** [[Sisime des Aigles River]], Quebec\n*** [[Orient River (Touladi River tributary)|Orient River]], Quebec\n**** [[Verte River (Orient River tributary)|Verte River]], Quebec\n*** [[Squatec River]], Quebec\n**** [[Owen River (Qu\u00e9bec)|Owen River]], Quebec\n** [[Bouleaux River (Madawaska River tributary)|Bouleaux River]], Quebec\n}}\n\n== Connecticut River \u2013 Quebec and New Hampshire ==\n\n* [[Connecticut River]], [[New Hampshire]]\n** [[Halls Stream]], Quebec and [[New Hampshire]]\n\n{{Expand list|date=August 2016}}\n\n==See also==\n* [[List of rivers of Canada]]\n* [[List of longest rivers of Canada]]\n* [[List of Hudson Bay rivers]]\n* [[List of tributaries of St. Lawrence River]]\n* [[List of tributaries of Gulf of St. Lawrence River]]\n* [[List of rivers of New Brunswick]]\n* [[List of rivers of Ontario]]\n* [[List of rivers of Newfoundland and Labrador]]\n* [[List of rivers of Montreal Island]]\n* [[List of rivers of Maine]]\n* [[List of rivers of New Hampshire]]\n* [[List of rivers of Vermont]]\n* [[List of rivers of New York State]]\n* [[List of rivers of the Americas]]\n* [[List of canals of Quebec]]\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.quebecgeographique.gouv.qc.ca/ Geography of Quebec \u2013 Gouvernment of Quebec]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Quebec topics}}\n{{Canada topic|List of rivers of}}\n\n[[Category:Lists of rivers of Canada|Quebec]]\n[[Category:Rivers of Quebec| ]]\n[[Category:Quebec-related lists|Rivers]]\n", "text_old": "[[Image:Quebecois flag.jpg|right|180px]]\n\nThis is a '''list of rivers of [[Quebec]]'''. Quebec has about:\n*one million lakes of which 70,840 have a toponymic designation (a name);\n*130,000 watercourses, including 4,203 rivers with a toponymic designation and 13,121 streams with a toponymic designation.<ref name = hydrographie>[http://www.toponymie.gouv.qc.ca/ct/ToposWeb/ Commission de toponymie du Qu\u00e9bec]</ref>\n\nQuebec has 2% of all [[freshwater|fresh water]] on the planet.<ref>\"''Du Qu\u00e9bec \u00e0 la Louisiane, sur les traces des Fran\u00e7ais d'Am\u00e9rique'', G\u00e9o Histoire, Hors-s\u00e9rie, \u00c9ditions Prisma, Paris, October 2006{{page needed|date=July 2018}}</ref>\n\n==James Bay watershed==\n\n===James Bay===\n\n====Rivers flowing into James Bay, listed from south to north====\n*[[Seal River (Ontario)]]\n*[[Roggan River]]\n**[[Corbin River]]\n**[[Anistuwach River]]\n*[[Piagochioui River]]\n\n=====Tributaries of La Grande River=====\n{{columns-list|colwidth=30em|\n*[[La Grande River]] (Grand River)\n**[[Chisasipis River]]\n**[[Utahunanis River]]\n**[[Kapisichikamastikw River]] (via [[LG3 Reservoir]])\n**[[Kanaaupscow River]] (via [[LG3 Reservoir]])\n**[[Patukamistikw River]] (via [[LG3 reservoir]])\n**[[Griault River]] (via [[LG3 reservoir]])\n**[[Kaminahikuschitin Creek]]\n**[[Sakustin River]]\n**[[Achazi River]] (via [[Robert-Bourassa Reservoir]])\n**[[Wapusukatinastikw River]]\n**[[La Forge River]] (via [[reservoir LG4]])\n**[[Nichicun River]] (via [[Nichicun Lake]])\n**[[Sakami River]]\n***[[Salomon River]]\n***[[Gatin\u00e9e River]]\n***[[Meechishgosheesh River]]\n***[[Bulgare River]]\n***[[Maug\u00e9 River]]\n**[[La Salle River (La Grande River tributary)]]\n**[[Anasakasich River]]\n**[[Asatawasach River]]\n**[[Pontois River]]\n***[[De la Corvette River]]\n**[[Kanaaupscow River]]\n***[[Chauvreulx River]]\n**[[Aigle River (La Grande River tributary)]] (via [[Mis\u00e8le Lake]])\n*[[Aquatuc River]]\n*[[Truite River]]\n*[[Mouton River]]\n*[[Caillet River]]\n*[[Castor River (Ontario)|Castor River]] (Beaver River)\n**[[Castor River East]]\n*[[Maquatua River]]\n*[[Sabascunica River]]\n**[[Clergue River]]\n*[[Peuplier River|Poplar River]]\n*[[Vieux Comptoir River]] (English: Old Factory River)\n*[[Conn River]]\n*[[Eastmain River]