ischen Einteilung der Schw\u00e4mme |journal=|volume=1 |pages=63\u2013128 |language=German}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"Persoon 1818\">{{cite book |author=Persoon CH. |year=1818 |title=Trait\u00e9 sur les Champignons Comestibles |page=257 |language=French}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"Richard 2015\">{{cite journal |vauthors=Richard F, Bellanger JM, Clowez P, Hansen K, O'Donnell K, Urban A, Sauve M, Courtecuisse R, Moreau PA |title=True morels (''Morchella'', Pezizales) of Europe and North America: evolutionary relationships inferred from multilocus data and a unified taxonomy |journal=Mycologia |year=2015 |url=http://www.mycologia.org/content/early/2014/12/24/14-166.abstract |doi=10.3852/14-166 |pmid=25550303 |volume=107 |issue=2 |pages=359\u2013382}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"Shavit 2010\">{{cite journal |vauthors=Shavit E, Shavit E |title=Lead and arsenic in ''Morchella esculenta'' fruitbodies collected in lead arsenate contaminated apple orchards in the northeastern United States: A preliminary study |journal=Fungi Magazine |volume=3 |issue=2 |date=Spring 2010 |pages=11\u201318 |url=http://www.fungimag.com/winter-2010-articles/shavit-morels.pdf}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"Stamets 2005\">{{cite book |author=Stamets P. |year=2005 |title=Mycelium Running |publisher=Ten Speed Press |location=Berkeley |page=344}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"Stefani 2010\">{{cite journal |vauthors=Stefani FO, Sokolski S, Wurtz TL, Pich\u00e9 Y, Hamelin RC, Fortin JA, B\u00e9rub\u00e9 JA |title=''Morchella tomentosa'': a unique belowground structure and a new clade of morels |journal=Mycologia |volume=102  |issue=5 |year=2010 |pages=1082\u20131088 |doi=10.3852/09-294 |url=http://www.lter.uaf.edu/pdf/1515_Stefani_Sokolski_2010.pdf |pmid=20943507}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"Ta\u015fk\u0131n 2012\">{{cite journal |authors=Ta\u015fk\u0131n H, B\u00fcy\u00fckalaca S, Hansen K, O\u2019Donnell K. |year=2012 |title=Multilocus phylogenetic analysis of true morels (''Morchella'') reveals high levels of endemics in Turkey relative 